While I can&#39;t really comment on how or why ckcti is failing you (my
own initial attempts at using it were unsuccessful, and I haven&#39;t
really had a need for it), I can at least tell you why 

gas1 = octane 

doesn&#39;t work.  The calls

gas = gri30  (or oxygen, hydrogen, nitrogen, or water, for that
matter)

work only because functions have been written (as mfiles, assuming
you&#39;re using matlab) that in turn make the appropriate &#39;importPhase&#39;
calls.  Again, assuming you&#39;re using matlab, look in the folder
&#39;matlab&#92;toolbox&#92;cantera,&#39; and you&#39;ll see the functions GRI30.m,
hydrogen.m, etc.

I&#39;m sure somebody else here can help you with ck2cti.

Best of luck,
Steven



